May 9, 1923

May 9, 1923
Collected 2 Diadophis amabilis similis on the road at Ballena Grade west of Witch Creek, driving with Van Denburgh and Slevin. One of my earliest hunting trips. This was before I kept complete records.

May 13, 1923
With Van Denburgh and Slevin on Mountain Springs Grade. This was the day they discovered the method of collecting Xantusia henshawi and Phyllodactylus tuberculosis by using a pinch-bar to pry rock flakes off of granite boulders.

July 4, 1923

Lemon Grove - Monte Vista - Dehesa - Frog Bridge - Back to Alpine Junction - Alpine - Descanso via Viejas Grade - Guatay Valley - Return via Viejas Grade Alpine and Paved Highway.

1201-2 1 mile east of Descanso on road to Milguatay Valley.

Also saw at this point 1 Xantusia henshawi but could not catch. Got one newt but he dried up.

1203-4 Top of old Viejas-Descanso Grade 1/4 mile west of summit. Saw several more X.h. at this point.

No snakes seen this day except one dead C. lateralis on Dehesa Grade west of Alpine Junction.

Notes:

Will

On the first line, is it Frog Bridge or Froy Bridge?

July 6th

Santa Ysabel via highway - Henshaw Dam - Palomar - down west grade - Pala - Bonsal - Oceanside - home.

Took 1 C. mitchellii at top of Mussey Grade 4.7 mi from Ramona. No other snakes alive or dead seen this day.

1205 - 1 mile west of top of grade west of Ballena. Approx 1.6 mi west of Ballena.

1206 - 7 East Palomar Grade about halfway bet. Mendenhalls and Henshaw Dam.

1208 West Palomar Grade 4 mi from top (west)

July 8th

Lakeside - Ramona - Julian - Cuyamaca - Descanso (old grade) - Alpine - home.

Took one poor specimen L. g. boylii 2 1/2 mi east of Ramona

Took 1 S. humilis in crack in rock .6 mi from bottom of old Viejas Grade.

Saw a garter in creek 1/2 mi w. of Julian also one crossing road just beyond Julian. Saw one dead gopher near Wynola.

1209-10-11-12 1.6 mi west of Wynola on Santa Ysabel Julian Road

1213-14-15-16 north end Cuyamaca Lake

1217-18-19-20 .8 mi east of Descanso on Milguatay Road.

1221-2-3-4-5-6 .6 mi from bottom of old Viejas Grade on Viejas-Descanso Road.

Patch nosed snake #1227 Date and place of collection unknown. San Diego County

July 14th

July 14th

Wildwood Ranch

Saw S. orcuttis and X.h 2 each
Got 1 X.h #1228

July 23rd

Buckman Springs via old Viejas and back via new Viejas.

Tried for X.h in Pine Valley negative.

At south end Buckman Valley at 3200 ft. saw X.h and S. orcutti but got none.

Got #1229 at this point.

Sultry day with rain.

Aug 19th

Pine Valley via old Viejas and back via new Viejas

Got #1231 X.h at north of entrance. Saw nothing also no snakes alive or dead.

Aug 26th

Went to Mission Beach at 4 PM. 1232-1233 - Got 2 Uta stansburiana hesperis.
Also 9 small. - 1235

1 Calif King (small) Collected at Boulder Creek Elev 2750 on Aug 27th (from one camp). 1236

Sept 2nd
Went along Coronado Strand. Looked for Utas at one likely place. Saw one not sure uta but was a lizard. Then went to Mission Beach near crowds. Got 5 large Utas - 1253-57

Sept 3rd

Went to Forwards Ranch at 200 PM
Returned at 8:30
A hot muggy day
Went up into rocks west of house
Saw 3 X.h. got 2
Saw 1 skelly kind unknown
Got 1 small exsul at 6:15 on edge of field.
Sent up unnumbered
1 X.a. is unusually large
length 5.85" tail 3.33" Had two well developed embryos. Bodies yes & tails clearly evident. Egg yolks attached & full abdominal cavity. Looks as if gave birth to young alive. Stomach contained beetles or large ant.

Numbered the other 1270

Oct 21st

Went to Valley Center via Escondido 93 miles. A cool pleasant day. Stopped for lunch 1 mi from top of V.C. grade then 2 mi east on Walnut Hill Ranch Road.
Started at 11 AM returned at 7P.M. Saw no snakes dead or alive.

Saw 2 X.h. got one No 1271
Saw several skellys & Utas
Got none. Saw one frog.

Dec 6th. Alpine near West long span structure 1 X.a.

1924 Season

Jan 12 Kids caught 1 Batrachoseps attenuatus in front yard.

Jan 25 Drove to Escondido and back on fine warm day. Saw nothing.

Feb 1 Drove to Alpine and back with Bill Fay. A fine warm day. Saw no snakes or lizards other than X.h.
At Grossmont got 2 X.h 1 large 1 very small. Also got a smashed one and one got away. At west end long span got one X.h and one got away. Tried no other points.

Field Notes April 6th, 1924

El Cajon, Lakeside, Wildwood, Ramona, Home Start 10:30 back at 6:30 Family and gantz. 77 miles. A warm day but part cloudy. Plenty rains during previous week. ground wet everywhere. Saw no snakes on road.

First stop about 1/2 way up Mugzeys grade elevation 950. got 4 Xantusia henshawi 1 frog, 1 Batrachoseps attenuatus. Saw 3 small skellys, 2 skelly orcutti(shot 1 but lost him). Lost about 4 X.h. and 1 frog. Stopped near Wildwood
gate and ate lunch. Got one Skelly orcutti (5605). Saw lizards probably Utas. Went on to Wildwood and hunted a short time on east side. Got 7 X.h. and one Bat. atten. but latter was smashed. Small one X.h. seen to be on north or east lakes as if to get warm sun. Many X.h. seem to be half grown. Possibly yearlings. Went on to Ramona turned around and came back. Stopped near top of grade and hunted on east side of road. Got 11 X.h. and one

Sunday April 13th

yearling calif. king found latter under granite lake while looking for X.h. was close to ground and some dirt in crack. was coiled up.

Sunday April 13th

Lemon Grove, Jamacha, Jamul, Cottonwood, Tecate and return. Family, Hugo & Jess. 88 miles
A cool day with high fog in town clear at Tecate Hunted there only. Wet during previous week. Ground wet got 19 X.h. 1 uta (shot) 1 Coluber lateralis (shot). Saw several Skellies both o.b. and orcutti. Saw no other snakes on road or elsewhere but kids saw 1 unknown. Most X.h. are under north lakes but not all. C. lateralis was first seen in rocks and sand. Then discovered watching me with head out only. Had to shoot him or loose him. A good full grown specimen

Sunday April 14th / 24

La Mesa, El Cajon, Alpine, Viejas, Old Viejas grade, Descanso, Glen Lonely, Dehesa, Bostonia. Hillebrand, Bill Fay, Dud Phelps,
91 miles. A fine clear day after 2 hot days. Not hot except
in spots. Some wind in exposed places.

First stop about 1/4 way up Viejas grade at square concrete reservoir on south side of road. Elevation 2700. Got one fine C. exsul under rock. (under shadow of rock, part in sun). Had evidently fed recently. Dud found one small C. exsul under a boulder in a hollow. Was coiled up. Got 1 Uta #5633. Tried 1 other point on grade got nothing. Lost several X.h.. Beyond Descanso at 48.7 mi (call it Jupatuls) got a large
P.c. annectens in rocks. Dull in color. little black. Also 1 skelly, o.b. (larger and blacker of 2). At 50.6 (call it Japatul) got, small (yearling). P.c. annectens crossing the road.
at top of hill above Glen Lonely (Japatul School). 53.7 got a fine large C. exsul. was on the

Untitled Page 17

move between two large boulders when first seen. Put up biggest kind of a fight. Coiled and was ready for fight before attacked with snake stick. Crawled under rock and was caught. Also got large G.s. webbii at this point. Found by Hills. Covered hill further down road
but got nothing. At Glen Lonely school got smaller G.s. webbii; also Dud shot S.o. biseriatus (smaller and lighter of 2). At 55.8 (call it Glen Lonely) found a small squashed Salvadora hexalepis in road. Only dead snake seen in road this day. Start 930 return 630.

55.8 + 39 = 95 total

Sunday April 27th

Encanto, Spring Valley (Helix), Grossmont, El Cajon, Bostonia, Dehesa, Glen Lonely, Japatul, Descanso, Old Viejas grade, Alpine, La Mesa. Family, Alley J Leet. Cloudy in town. Fairly clear in the foothills but not always so. Fairly cool. Some wind total miles 88.
Start 10:15 return 6:30.

At the foot of the Bostonia Dehesa grade found 1 dead
C. lateralis and a few feet further a dead P.c. amneeteno. Miles 21.9. Call it Dehesa. Just after crossing to north side of creek in Dehesa - Alpine [?] grade (miles 25.9). Saw a C. lateralis in the road but got away. First stop at 30.7 after kids being car sick (Call it Glen Lonely) Here got 1 X.h. and 2 Crotals exsul fine large specimens. They were coiled (loosely) on east side of flat rock with light cover. Separated about two feet. 1 slightly larger than other. Watched them for some time while stuck and

Sunday May 4

boys were being brought up. Didn't move. 1st one rattled when hung but second didn't move and didn't rattle when hung. Also got 1 P.c. annectens just in front of car in road. Stopped at Glen Lonely for lunch. Ranged all over rocks energetically. Saw 1 C. lateralis but lost him. No other snakes. Saw 1 horned toad. Got 1 Skelly o.b. Saw several orcuttis. Stopped again at Top of hills. Got another Skelly o.b.
and saw orcuttis. No snakes. Stopped a couple of miles further on and hunted rocks but got nothing. Saw no snakes alive or dead on the way up.

Sunday May 4
Kensington Park, Grantville, Mission Gorge, Santee, Lakeside, Foster, Wildwood. Return via Highway. Total mileage 63. Family[?] + Gartz. High fog in town, clear and warm in back country. Start 10:20 return
6:30. 1 dead snake on highway at Grantville - couldn't identify. Stopped at Foster in large rocks at east of highway and hunted diligently. No snakes; got 1 X.h., 2 uta, 1 skelly. Stopped at top of Mussey grade
got 1 X.h. Stopped for lunch ahead of

Monday May 5

gate. Got nothing. Got to Forwards about 2P.M. Went up west mountain grade with Jim Woody and MFH. Got Trimorphodon? in crack of rock. First seen by Woody when he lifted rock which he dropped back. Removed this and then removed small adjacent rock. Found in a crack alongside of small rock.
Removed with forceps. Tried to bite. Went on up mountain. Got 7 h.x. Jim saw 1 Calif racer. Description OK so center[?] on manp. Jay saw long black snake coming out. Black C.f. piceus? Can't enter. On the way back saw 1 dead snake near top of grade. Going too fast couldn't stop to identify. Probably garter or C.latealis.

Monday May 5
Kensington Park, Grantville, Mission Gorge, Santee, Lakeside, Foster, Wildwood, Ramona, San Pasqual,Bernardo, home. Total mileage 88. Watson, Pratt, Bill Fay. Start 2 P.M. Return 5:45 P.M. A fine clear day. At Mission Dam caught a medium red rattler. 1/4 way up Mussey grade lost a banded racer. No doubt of identification. Near San Pasqual saw snake probably garter but

Sunday May 11

identification not certain. At 1 mi north of Bernardo found a dead red rattler. At 2 mi north
of Poway lost a C.lateralis. Wildwood elevation 1520.

Sunday May 11

Encanto, Spring Valley, Jamul, Dulzura, Campo,Jacumba, and return. 150 miles. Dud Phelps and Hopkins. Start 9:00 return 7:15. A fine clear day in the back country. Cloudy in town. Got 1 Lampropeltis g. boyliicrossing the road at 25.1 Jamul. 1 dead boylii along side the road at 30.1 Dulzura. Lost 1 live Coluber lateralis at 30.5. Dulzura = 30.6. Caught large exsul at Dulzura summit 32.6. Call it Dulzura. Also at this point got 2 Whiptails 1 orcutti 1 biseriatus (?) and several (5) x.a. Hunted here a considerable time also 1/4 mile further along 1 dead pacific rattler by the side of the road at 33.2. Call it Dulzura.

Notes:

lwilliams

species = biseriatus??

Sunday May 18

Stopped for lunch near Potrero. Hunted here but got nothing. Also nothing between here and Jacumba. Almost 1 mile west of Jacumba on return trip hunted in rocks north side of road. Got a fine large C. mitchellii. Also a number of X.h. (9) Hunted here quite a while. 1 juvenile gopher dead 4.2 miles west of Jacumba. Call it Boulevard. 1 juvenile C. oreganus smashed in rpad 4.9 miles west of Jacumba. Call it Boulevard. 1 mile west of camp 1 C. lateralis smashed in road. Call it Campo. Nothing between here and home except a blowout.

Sunday May 18
La Mesa, Grossmont, El Cajon, Alpine, Los Terrenitos, Pine Valley, Buckmans, Boulevard, Jacumba,Campo, Patrero, Dulzura, Home. 151 miles. Start 9:40 home 6:30. Family, Leet and Stell. A clear day but rather warm. Had been too warm for several days and reported

Notes:

Untitled Page 23

very hot in San Joaquin Valley. This may have had something to do with poor results. Anyway only saw 1 live snake all day this on Potrero grade about 1/2 up. Probably was small gopher but couldn't catch or identify. First stop at about 10 min west of Boulevard on the highway. Hunted in the rocks but got nothing. Saw orcuttis. Stopped for lunch at Boulevard. Hunted long time in hills to north. Got 1 x.h. Saw no snakes. Saw orcuttis and other lizards.
Saw following dead snakes:
1 C.lateralis at Boulevard
1 Juv C.oreganus at Boulevard
1 R.lecontei at Hapais(?) (brought in for identification)
1 snake too far gone to identify about 6 mi east of Campo.
1 small unidentified (didn't stop) at Campo.
1 juvenile gopher on Potrero grade
1 Boa about half way up Cottonwood grade.
1 large gopher at Dulzura.

Tuesday May 20th

Old Town, Miramar, Escondido, Valley Center, Lunch at camp 2, Sylvano, Bear Valley Dam, Escondido, home. Start 9:40, back 2:40 104 miles. Both Peckham, Watson, Ayres. No hunting only riding. A clear hot overly warm day. Rather warm in Valley Center. Saw no live snakes.
Checked the following dead 1 at about 8 . Didnt stop.
1 juvenile gopher at 11.8. Call it Rosedale.
1 Long nose at 12.8 Call it Rosedale
1 Boyles King at 22.0 (Poway).
1 Gopher at 27.5 (Bernardo) 52 miles at Camp.
1 C. oreganus at 85.8 (miramar).

Saturday May 31st

A clear warm day. Started from Warners at 8 A.M. returned at 5 P.M. 105 miles.

Went to Yaqui well via Grapvine canon back to Warners (not Agua Caliente) via Sentenac canon and San Felipe, thence to Pine Hills to Cuyamaca, back by Julian, Santa Ysabel to Hot Springs.

Got 1 X.h. in Grapevine canon at 10 miles and 1 X.h. at 13. Tried various other points but got nothing - particularly base of Sentenac and Yaqui. Friday Jan 2nd

A clear warm day. LA to SD. 1 dead garter in road at San Onofre bridge. 64 mi.

A clear cool day. LA to SD with Rabers. Saw nothing. 64 mi.

Friday Feb 27 1925
A clear warm day like summer after several warm days. Went to Hillsdale via Jamacha and returned via El Cajon. With Peckham 2 to 4 PM. Saw nothing in the road. Stopped at a pile of rocks near Hillsdale school Saw 1 Crotalus exsul which was lost for lack of catching equipment. Was a yearling about 2 1/2 ft. long. Seemed to have three rattles, was thin and rather torpid. Didn't try to bite but finally got away quickly enough. Also saw some skellies one looked like an orcutti and 1 Xantusia henshawi. 31 mi.

March 22 (cont)

Lichanura. Was climbing up bank at side of road. Stopped for lunch about one mile beyond top grade at alt 3730. Got one large Thamnophis in a bush while eating lunch. Came back with Allen to a point west of top of grade at alt. 3740. Hunted here diligently. Got 2 skellys, 3 utas, 2 X.h. lost several X.h. saw several orcuttis. Shot one C. lateralis. First caught him by the tail and was promptly bitten. Dropped him. He shot into
upper branches of manzanita and escaped by aerial route. Looked for a while and finally spotted him in branches about 3 ft above ground. Took no chances and shot him as I wished to see what he had eaten (Quite an evident lump). Opened him after got home and found 1 large Skink and 1 large skelly.
both eaten head first. Found a large Hypsiglena under a rock while looking for X.h. was under a good sized chunk rather than a slate. On the way in while in a sack
this snake ate a small X.h. Hunted further down but got nothing. While picking lilacs near ????? saw a small snake or skink. too fast to tell

carry on

The country around the windmill is as typically desert as any of Imperial county. Silt with scattered hummocks covered with mesquite many holes in hummocks where animals take refuge. The S.S.Co. switch is about 20 poles east of the edge of the real desert.

For lizard record and locations see specimen record.

Saturday May 9th

A cold cloudy day threatening rain. Went to Dulzura summit alone in max. Started 1:40 went via Encanto. Returned to upper Otay lodge via road around the south side of lower Otay dam very rough supper at lodge. Return to S.D. at night 10:40 total miles 79.5

Hunted had at Dulzura summit got 12 X.h. and 1 skelly. Saw no snakes on trip dead or alive. Too cold.

Sunday may 10th

Another cold cloudy day with occasional short spells of sunshine. Almost cold enough for over coats.
With kids, Garty and Jane. Start 9:40 return at 5:50
total miles 99.1

carry on sunday may 10th

Route. Lower road via Encanto, Spring Valley, Jamacha, Dulzura, Glen Lonely, Descanso, to
Woliva(? grove. Return via Old Viejas Grade and highway.
Stopped first at top of Glen Lonely grade. Got nothing. too windy. Next stop old adobe house south of Descanso. Hunted here a long time. Got 5 X.h. 1 skink, 1 young orcutti (saw several) and 1 C. lateralis. Chased the latter under a rock and caught his tail under it when over turned the rock. He twisted laterally and twisted tip of tail practically off.

Went to Woliva(?) grove where we lunched. Hunted strenuously
in rocks north of grove but there were few snakes. got only 1 X.h. saw some skelly orcuttis. While I was away the kids caught a large gopher.

nothing. Got 1 horned toad in the road. Returned via Warners road. Got 1 large gopher crossing the road near old stage station at 4 P.M. Sunday May 31st

Started from Powam lodge at 8:30. A cold windy morning with high fog. Got to Julian at 9:10 and stopped for gas. Went down Banner grade with the intention of going south in San Felipe valley along old stage road toward Carrizo but after going along this road for about 1/2 mile turned back north toward Warners on account of gale blowing from N.W. was raising quite a bit of sand. Caught me 1 large gopher just after passing San Felipe camp. Was crossing the road. 10 A.M. a little further north saw large C. lateralis. Wounded him but lost him in bush. Went to Warner's road. Hunted a short time in hill to west of road. Saw skellies and whiptails but did not get any. Returned to Powam lodge at 12:14. Miles in morning 64.1 for trip 236.3

A clear fairly cool day. went to Garbage lake with Phil and Garty 9:30 A.M. - 12:15 P.M. 37 miles

1 C. lateralis large dead in road at Rose Canyon 11 miles
1 L.g. boylii med dead in road at
head of Rose canyon near city farm.
2 T.o. hammondii large at Garbage lake

*live specimens in zoo list.

carry on sunday june 14th

Sunday afternoon June 14th to Monday June 21st at S.F. at NELA convention and on side trip with Chickering (?).

Sunday june 28th.
A cool cloudy day with considerable rain especially between S.D. and Alpine. Somewhat oppressive at times.
Went to Cuyamaca Lake with Phil and Gary picked up Allen at Willows. Went via old Viejas Grade and returned same way made a side trip from Descanso south to old adobe house.
Start at 9:45 back at 6:15 total miles 122.
Hunted in rocks near top of Old Viejas Grade and got 1 skelly and 1 orcutti. Ate lunch beyond top of grade. Hunted along south side of Lake Cuyamaca. Also hunted for a short time around dobe house but it was raining at the time. On the way back stopped at the square reservoir and hunted but got only 1 Uta.

Snake list.
(Live snakes marked * are in zoo list)

*1 Fine large Boylii under a bush above road near top of Old Viejas Grade.

* 1 large gopher (located by track) alongside of road just before reaching Descanso.

Notes:

lwilliams

Chickering (?), person?

carry on sunday june 28th

* 1 fairly large gopher along side of road at Berkey's store located by track. Was found in mazanita bush about 1 ft. above ground. Along a branch.

1 juv Calif King found dead along side of road at this point. Saved for specimen.

* 1 juv gopher at bridge near Terrenitos.

1 Pacific Rattler large. Dead in road east side of Watai(??) valley

2 garter dead along lake shore at Cuyamaca. Not along road.

* 1 live garter at this point. Caught in grass

1 snake indistinguishable dead in road 1 mile south of lake.

* 1 med. Patchnose caught in road about 1/2 way down old Viejas grade.

Saturday June 27th
1 C. lateralis in the park. Got away but had hand on it.

lwilliams

Wednesday July 1

A cloudy rather muggy day. Went to Point Loma thence to
La Jolla with Smith of Public Service gas. Start at 10:30 A.M. return at 12:15. One dead C. lateralis large. At junction of O.B. and main roads just NW of Theo. Seminary.

Sunday July 5th

A fine clear day not uncomfortably warm west of the mountains a trifle hot on the other side.
To Jacumba and back via Alpine and the old Viejas
Grade. Total miles 160.3. Start 10:15 back at 6:35. With family Allie and Allen.
No snakes seen on the highway dead or alive. no tracks
Stopped for lunch halfway bet La Posta and Blvd and hunted here about an hour at noon. Got 1 Uta, 1 Orcutti, 3 skellys lost an X.h.. Under a flat rock about 15" in diameter resting on earth found 3 good sized C. oreganus. They were in shallow hollow. All started to escape at once without rattling. Held one down with stick another stopped in first bush but the third got away. Stopped at two
places on the way home near Jacumba and in Viejas grade to let brakes cool but got nothing.

Notes:

lwilliams

Start ??? 5 back at 6:35

Sunday July 12th

An average hot day for this time of year. Uncomfortably hot in the back country. Clear all day and muggy on the coast.
Went to Dulzura, Barrett, Jamul, Jamacha, Sweetwater dam, Sunnyside, Bonita, Nat. City. Total miles 89.6. Start 9:45 return 5:30. No snakes seen alive or dead along the road. Except only 2 tracks. First stop at top of Dulzura grade hunted hard for over an hour. No snakes seen. Got 1 X.h. (lost 1) and 1 half grown skink. Noted that X.h. were not under flakes but rather under large chunks. Next stop at old bridge (washed out) bet Lyone valley and Barrett. Nearer Barrett. Got 3 T.o.hammondii; saw 2 dead in creek and lost 1. Boys saw others (3?) which they lost. Got 1 skelly and 1 Hyla arenicolor. Boys got several Hylas which they placed in bag with snakes but they ate them.
1 large dead L.c. californiae dead on the road at Sunnyside.
With Phil, Allen, Gartz, Hugh Skilling.

Sunday Aug 9th

To county line on the way north. Saw nothing dead of alive. Started 6:30am

Lampropeltis getula

California King snake

L.g. boylii refers to the subspecies of king snake which has a ringed pattern.

L.g. californiae refers to the subspecies of king snake which has a striped pattern.
